Upload ontology model

The application administrator is able to load one or more ontology models using the system.

  1. In the Administration menu/ Manage models there is a section in which there is option "Import ontology models".
  2. Browse and select one ontology model. Allowed file formats are (zip), (ttl), (xml), (ns), (trig) and (sparql).

 

After selection of one ontology model uploaded it with action "Import".

  • After successful operation the message: "The selected ontology models are loaded successfully." is displayed and the uploaded ontology models become active immediately.
  • In case of error  the message: "Tenant <tenant name> update failure!" is displayed and the models from error file should not be applied.
